casebody.data:
Blakely, Respondent, v. Goldmark, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. February 26, 1891.) Appeal from eleventh district court.

Argued before Bischoff and Pryor, JJ.

L. Steckler, for appellant. A. Lamont, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment reversed, new trial ordered, costs to abide the -event.
